review: Good game, I recommend playing it. It's more realistic and overall pretty good. Although the UI isn't great, but it also isn't terrible. I got used to it pretty fast. Another thing, is that when you're in the game, you can't access any other app or website. Apparently pushing windows couldn't get me out of it. In order to go to chrome or brave with the game on, I had to completely shut the whole game off. But this might just be my computer.

author: {'steamid': '76561197984705404', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 8812, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 7935, 'last_played': 1659485135}
review: Great game! Without taking in any other factors this is a fun way to pass the time! Line of Sight has interesting additional game mechanics that makes it different than your normal arena FPS(psyc-powers).  The community is far, half the time someone is cheating and the other half think you are cheating.  I would suggest, take some time to get the ability usage in rotation and see if it fits your play-style, before getting to worked up about people just dominating.  Has a good size gun library and each one has a selection of customizations for the gun people out there.  If you want to expand your selection of guns you will have to grab your credit card though. All in all, good game, wild matches and guns to have fun; don't take the trolls to serious they can't help themselves.  Have fun and i'll catch you in my sights!

review: This game has a steep learning curve. In no small part due to cheaters. They only present a challenge though. They can still be dominated. The challenge of avoiding their attention. Getting around their flank. Not an impossible task. Cheating is also a skill. One that many of the cheaters haven't yet mastered. A nice challenge. Great game, all the same. I highly recommend Line of Sight.

review: Es un muy buen juego hasta ahora lo que he jugado me ha encantado, me gusta todo desde las armas y las habilidades que le podemos poner a nuestros personajes, y un nivel muy bueno de personalizacion del arma, creo que deberian de mejorar un poco el lanzagranadas su radio de daÃ±o es bastante pequeÃ±o entiendo que puede ser muy op si matara a muchos de un solo tiro pero por lo menos dejarlos heridos no estaria mal y solo matar a alguien directamente si le pega la explosion directo asi que por ese lado ponerle un lanzagranadas a un arma se siente bastante inutil tal vez tambien podrian agregarle una escopeta montable a los rifles de asalto eso estaria bien, el gamplay como los mapas y modos de juegos tambien son muy variados, sin duda recomiendo este juego un muy buen shooter ojala y mas gente lo jugara eso es lo que le hace falta al juego mas promocion aca en latinoamerica y norteamerica.

On a whim I decided to look at old games I haven't really played from my steam library and reinstalled this game. That was a mistake because this game is hilariously bad. There is one server, and if you get terrible ping in western Europe servers, well you can get bent because you have no other option. 

This game has no idea what it is doing, it has some of the worst hit registration/ hit boxes I have ever seen on a steam game and I've played a lot of garbage games. Sometimes entire magazines wont register, other times a shot in the foot will instantly kill with a headshot, its a complete coin flip if you win gun fights or you could just head glitch and not have a head hitbox entirely, you could be that guy in the lobby. To put into perspective on how bad this game is, its most popular 2 maps do not even have textures. Do not give any money to this trash fire and move along.

author: {'steamid': '76561197993070333', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 73, 'playtime_forever': 68, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 34, 'last_played': 1637574910}
review:
I really want to recommend this game but I just canâ€™t at the moment. I enjoy playing it and it brings back so many good memories of MW2 but there are just too many problems with it currently. If the devs fix/change anything I'll update my review.
Pros
Weapon/Character Customization
Not Pay to Win (Yes I'm serious)
Runs good
High TTK
Classic Vibe
Weapon Balance (Pretty good, there are a few weps that need a nerf atm though.)

Cons
Hitreg - Terrible atm, constantly die around corners
Hit boxes - Same with hitreg
Head glitching - Major problem that needs fixing
GP earn rate - Needs to be increased or weapon prices lowered
Mantle/Flash Animation - Are terrible and get you killed so much and need to be removed.
Player falling physics - don't try to slide down a hill
Flashlight - I get its a tactical light but it shouldn't be like looking at the sun
Maps - Pretty meh, a lot of them could use adjusting.
"Super Powers/Abilities" - I hate them, but I play classic anyways
UI - Could be simpler

If you want to read it properly formatted: http://steamcommunity.com/id/Juggernaut_Drive/recommended/436520/

I'll try to expand on my points in case anyone is interested in more of what I mean. Before that however I do want to mention that I do enjoy the game. I enjoy it so much and it reminds me of when I used to play COD all day on xbox when I was a kid. Now to get to the points.

The Pros:
Weapon/Character Customization - Nothing much to say just it's pretty in depth and you can make so many different variants. The only real thing their lacking here are the skins. I assume they will add more skins in time though.
Not Pay to Win - It's not pay to win which is great! People who say it's pay to win don't put any time into the game and look don't at the weapon stats. If you did than you would find out that most of the weapons you buy don't have any better stats that the ones you start with. Now of course there are some weapons that are better than others atm but you get that with every AAA game that has a price tag of ~$60 so I'm sure the developers will address those in the future.
Runs good - Nothing more to say really. It runs good and I have had no problems with it.
High TTK - Very high time to kill which is great. But if you pair that with bad hitreg then you get a load of problems (hitreg is talked about more below).
Classic Vibe - Reminds me of the COD4/MW2 days.
Weapon Balance - As talked about in the not p2w section, weapon balance is pretty good at the time of this review.

The Cons:
Hitreg - It's really bad atm and I mean REALLY bad. Your shots don't hit and you die around corners constantly. I don't know if I just didn't notice it when I first started playing, but I noticed it after one of their updates. So I'm not sure if it was always bad or if that update broke it.
Hit boxes - The female hitbox is smaller than the males (not the bad point) but when you have bad hitreg/head glitching it makes you thing that the hit boxes are also broken. I don't know if itâ€™s that or the hitreg, but something is definitely off.
Head glitching - Major problem that needs fixing. You see the tippy top of their head and they see your whole body. Plus, pair that with the hitboxes and you can't hit their head.
GP earn rate - Needs to be increased or weapon prices lowered. I have around 28 hours into the game (not all playtime) and I currently have around ~170,000 GP. Which seems like a lot of GP but when you add that I played very heavily during the valentine event and the new achievements I got (since it was a new account) it's really not that much. If it wasn't a valentine event and I wasn't a new player I would have significantly less GP for that time played. Yes yes I know you get GP from missions, achievements, leaderboard rankings and at the end of every match.
Missions - Math is based off a 30 day month. So if you do EVERY single mission a month you get around 114,000GP. Daily Missions = 90,000GP, Weekly Missions = 12,000GP, Monthly Missions = 12,000GP. So 1 month of my time isn't worth enough for ONE primary weapon (about 214,000GP)?
Achievements - Yes you get GP for achievements and you get the reward ONCE. This seems good and fair since there are 408 achievements but it's not. More than like half of the achievements are weapon related which means you CAN'T get the reward until you unlock the weapon. The weapons go as follows; K2 I = 30 kills, K2 II = 300 kills, K2 III = 3000 kills. I shouldn't have to say much more about why relying on achievements for GP is so stupid.
Leaderboard - You get 20,000GP if you place in the top 4% in every section every month.
End of match reward - You get like 100GP which is pointless. 1000 games of 100GP = 100,000GP.
Mantle/Flash Animation - Are terrible and get you killed so much and need to be removed. There stupid animations that are not needed. The flash puts a hand up in front of your view and you canâ€™t shoot until the hand goes down. It also lasts LONGER than the actual flash like wtf. The mantle locks you into a mantle animation when you try and jump over something.
Player falling physics - You get stuck and jitter down the hill or object thatâ€™s slanted.
Flash light - I get its a tactical light but it shouldn't be like looking at the sun. It's gameplay breaking, way to bright atm.
Maps - Pretty meh, a lot of them could use adjusting. The S&D maps are by far the best but come with problems as well. A lot of the sites only have 2 entrances and then its closed off.
"Super Powers/Abilities" - Hate them since you need to have the medic one equipped or youâ€™re at a huge disadvantage.
UI - Very confusing when you first load it up and could be simpler.

I really enjoy that, the mecanics are well implemented, it has a great optimization, the only kind of negative issue is there are few servers. But never encountered any lag, any toxic comunity, hackers, etc.

I try to play this game almost every day and Im am really enjoying it.
I want to give this good feedback specially to the developers, they really deserve it.

Totally recomended.

review:
The game is fun, but matchmaking is a joke. Your first game youre matched with level 200+ players, The lowest level player ive ever matched with was 68.
You unlock stronger guns as you level up too which is annoying since theres no fair matchmaking and youre using a default gun against maxed out snipers and assault rifles.

author: {'steamid': '76561198104022135', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 90305, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 45016, 'last_played': 1689393200}
review: I seriously liked this game. One of my favorites. It had a neat concept (psionics + FPS), pretty great graphics (especially considering the bulk of development happened in 2017), and an awesome community. I wish they could find funding to really evolve the game further. Sadly, not much has changed in recent years. I do recommend the game for anyone looking for an easy to learn, but hard to master FPS game that doesn't feel super mainstream.

author: {'steamid': '76561198196600910', 'num_games_owned': 418, 'num_reviews': 54, 'playtime_forever': 293, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 266, 'last_played': 1620576001}
review:
'Okay' best sums up the game.
It's not good by any means, but enough to last a while.

Game's basically dead, a lot of that going to VERY BAD anti-cheat system.
Apart from that, the game doesn't have much holding it up, and other Asian shooters offer way more than this one does.
The game occasionally has an event or two that'll bring people to the game for a weekend to about Monday or Tuesday depending on the event, but otherwise it's nothing that's going to stay.

I recommend it if you want the most basic, fast sniping, and accuracy based head picking I've ran into in an Asian FPS. Though otherwise, you're gonna be better off looking elsewhere to see if there's something else that offers you a better experience.
Apart from that, the gameplay is actually the only thing making me rate this a yes from me. It's so energetic, fun, and fast paced, something you don't often find in even GOOD Asian FPS titles.
This game excels here.

review:
The concept of self-fund publishing was extreme, but sadly poor executed.

Pros:
-Somewhat extreme gun customisation
-ESP skill thingie

Cons:
-Inefficient Anti-Hacking Program
-P2W Weapons
-No support since 2019, which became crucial

Avoid this game, until they gave an update. Surprising though, the server still active.  Hacker somewhat infested in this game, making it less playable than it should be. Anyhow, soon or later they might ask another publisher to take care of this game, unless they let this game dead or pick Nexon for their publisher... Until now, just check another F2P FPS like Ironsight.

Update: Someone uploaded the screenshot about the conversation with Chris Kim, as he stated he will not continue to contribute LoS about a 7 months ago. The conclusion? LoS is dead, but he'll planned to make another game and Line of Sight 2, which I really doubt about it.

review: This game is a piece of SHIT and whoever developed this trash should be ashamed. Sniper shots don't count, I hit multiple headshots but died instead because THE FUCKING HEADSHOTS DON'T COUNT. author: {'steamid': '76561198862411731', 'num_games_owned': 242, 'num_reviews': 168, 'playtime_forever': 19, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 19, 'last_played': 1605070589}
review:
Esta bueno La portada y las fotos. Pero cuando entras es otra cosa...

Cuando entre al juego, lo primero que note es que estaba en ingles, ningun problema con el ingles. Â¿Porque que tanto te vas a poner a leer en un Shooter MM?.

Lo que si es que el el juego tiene server en Asia Y en Europa, Quedando como mejor Europa si estas en America, por obvias razones. 

Entre a una partida, y lo primero que note es que es un Zula. Pero es un Â¿Que pasaria si Zula Fuera mas "Original"?,
Entre comillas, ya que es mas copia a Cod.

Lo bueno es que no esta tan mal el juego, Es entretenido, si te gusta algo mas "frenetico". Que Zula XD

Lo malo es que solo tenga Server, EN ASIA Y EUROPA, y no es EE.UU (Por lo menos). Si vas a jugarlo, te recomiendo una red que tenga mas de 5 megas. 
Y lo segundo malo es que es un Free Fire o un Rush Fire. Ya que podes meter Headshot sin apuntar, y solo disparando a tal
brazuca en casual de CS:GO. 

Eso es todo

7,90/10

author: {'steamid': '76561198030230602', 'num_games_owned': 786, 'num_reviews': 87, 'playtime_forever': 33, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 33, 'last_played': 1590780989}
review:
No, though yes, if you want to just have a load of laughs with a few lads in some scuffed ass game that looks like it was a copy of a copy of some fps.

This is one of those games that are so bad in pretty much every way but the core gameplay takes little skill and fairly fun to  mess around in, that is, until you meet the p2w shit which this game is full of, sure you can kill your enemy and yoink their gun (which will quite likely outperform the sort of bottom of the barrel crap you start with) but if you never do then you'll just get wiped. 

The last and perhaps more disappointing and understandable thing is that this game is semi-dead, sure you'll get some stragglers here and there but you're gonna need to probably catch the game on "peaks" or just have a large circle of friends to play with.
Overall, not a game that needs to be taken serious and a solid 4/10

author: {'steamid': '76561197981522694', 'num_games_owned': 810, 'num_reviews': 11, 'playtime_forever': 38, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 38, 'last_played': 1590680569}
review:
Why did I Buy this... wait, *DID* I buy this?
No, free to play... and it shows, you're either stuck with a flattop M4 or you're handing over your credit card.

Honestly I'm not sure why this is in my library, I think maybe I was expecting either a VR experience or a replacement for Ghost Recon phantom and I got neither... just some cheap knock-off, low-quality Call of Duty wannabee that does not really live up to it's advertisement.

If you're jumping in expecting full range customizable weapons; nope... none of that.
Maps are tiny and usually wholly symmetrical; which means every map gets chocked within seconds and it becomes really boring.

SMART players will use the 30-day "Trial" for 'premium' weapons to come up with three distinct load outs, suitable for whatever situation you might find yourself in.... and assuming that unlike me you'll LAST those thirty days, rather than less than 30 minutes, you (MIGHT) be tempted to invest in ONE loadout.

I tried to get rid of that horrible first-half-that-is-a-before/after face my character had by adding a helmet; but apparently armored cranial protection and mutual mug mitigation is a PREMIUM feature.

I wouldn't recommend this game to anyone, but then again, I prefer coop- and single-player exploits over this type of junk.

author: {'steamid': '76561198073300219', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 15, 'playtime_forever': 5517, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 774, 'last_played': 1667629162}
review:
The game is pretty fun if you're into mindless PVP, the only challenge is finding a time where people are playing. There's only 2 regions and for the most part the Asia region is empty and the other is full of people with 200+ ping so it can get frustrating.
The AI matches are utterly useless in combat, so they're only good for earning some quick cash to buy guns or attachments.
Despite the low population the gameplay itself it actually pretty fun so I would recommend this game if you have a group of friends to join you.

Edit: You can pay real money to get a helmet that helps prevent headshots so that's pretty unfortunate.

author: {'steamid': '76561197976260411', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 19, 'playtime_forever': 46177, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1049, 'last_played': 1668093946}
review: This game is a fun, team based, areana shooter with some good combat, interesting add on powers, good character and weapon models, and a small number of interesting maps.  Its biggest flaw is probably that there doesn't seem to be any anti-cheat system - so in some matches the fact that some players are running "see you through walls" or "aiming" cheats becomes all too obvious.  Another problem is that the client UI doesn't support any option for a "color blind mode" - so the 5% of the population (10% among males) that is color blind will probably be at a big disadvantage by not being able to see red that is used to identify the bad guys very well (which is the most common type of color blindness).  In this day and age, all games should support alternate colors for identifying enemies other than than red!

author: {'steamid': '76561198047276038', 'num_games_owned': 305, 'num_reviews': 119, 'playtime_forever': 576, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 227, 'last_played': 1613478612}
review:
This game is a VERY good creation which is focusing on many gamemodes, it's like CS:GO but without those Cyka-Blyats and cheating kiddos everywhere around which I massively appreciate in my 3 (As of writing this review) hours of gameplay.

The weapon mechanics are just more than great, it provides you with selection of weaponry that you can choose from, within just that, you can also customize your weaponry, have more damage and therefore your accuracy suffers under it, the moment you change something to good, you also get a minus within, which is also quite balancing.

Weapongameplay is quite good, you can choose from the gamemodes you wanna play, whether it be with or without heavy weaponry, if you for example appreciate handguns more than heavy weaponry, just select it and you find yourself with a pistol over the entire game that you're playing.

What the game also provides is one of my most favorite, respawn times, unlike TF2 or other online-shooter games, if you die, you may get that typical showscreen who killed you, and then it is entirely up to you when you respawn (Maximum in 8-9 seconds), whether you respawn at 3 seconds, right immediately or you wait it out, this is entirely up to you.

Next, the game is obviously played actively by a small community, which as far as I'm aware is quite easy-peasy, either no one talks or people greet each other, with others GLHF / GG, which is quite a change seeing it from my side.

Next up, level system, obviously you'd think that a guy with 250 levels is FAR beyond you as 1st time player, wrong you are, everyone has the same chance of killing on another, and even if they stomp you, they ain't making a big deal out of it alike in other games... "Trashplayer", "You suck" or my favorite in my other games "Noob", seems alike this community seems to be quite a nice one.

I give this game a thumbs up, the game mechanics are so simple, yet, very amazingly done by the right people, and I also do appreciate the major fact, that "high level" players ain't toxic to the new ones that in most of the other games seem to be a thing.

Toxic TF2 Main - Out

author: {'steamid': '76561198008587191', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 17382, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 8999, 'last_played': 1699762817}
review:
This is basically an upgrade of Combat Arms. In fact, if memory serves, I believe it was originally going to be called "Combat Arms: Line Of Sight", making it a sequel.

Where Combat Arms was a lot of fun, this game does improve on many aspects, especially the customization of weapons. It also boasts the Unreal Engine, which looks great for a free-to-play game. And then they added more game modes, like a multi-player team death match where players can go co-op against bots. In Combat Arms: Reloaded, you can play against bots.... but only as a single player.

We also have "ESP" matches and "Psionics" matches, the former that lets you use abilities like short-range teleportation or creating medkits from (slowly) regenerating psionic energy (basically like mana or magic points). The latter of the modes includes offensive abilities, like flinging fireballs or dropping entire satellites on your enemy's head.

When I first started playing Line Of Sight, there were 5 different servers to play on. Sadly, since then, 3 of the servers have been removed due to low player count. In fact, there is no longer any U.S. server, so anytime I want to play, I have to pick either Europe or Asia to play on. If we can draw a lot more players, maybe they'll bring back some of the removed servers to give us better ping rates.

In addition, one thing that I don't like in going from Combat Arms: Reloaded to Line Of Sight is that there is no in-game option to record your matches to an .avi or .mp4 file for later viewing. You have to use some form of third party app for that.

I do enjoy the game, it's just hard to find large groups of players to join. As far as gameplay, for a free-to-play game, I would give it a solid 8 out of 10, despite its flaws.

author: {'steamid': '76561198037297607', 'num_games_owned': 4368, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 3628, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3311, 'last_played': 1710119332}
review:
With the shutting down of the USA Servers to this game I might as well leave my final thoughts for this game.  I started playing this a few years ago when it first released and my opinion on it was that, while nothing about it was inherently P2W , the way progressed and how fast you did was effected by it. Waiting for the regular currency in the game to pile up to help pay for attachments or new weapons, was very slow in comparison to dishing out a few bucks for the game's premium currency. 
Aside from that, the voice acting is horrible but the presentation is actually pretty good. The graphics and blood effects are really cool. The game ran pretty smooth for the most part. 
So why does this not get a recommend? Well, aside from the fact the game has been abandoned by both players and developers, the game is also populated by a bunch of whiny LVL 100+ who cry about hacks if they get killed once. I cant possibly imagine why this game was left behind when the only people hosting lobbies are the same whiny losers who block and accuse hacks on anyone coming into this game. I guess you can still play this game if you're EU or someplace else, but anywhere else that isn't covered by the servers, there's really no point to playing this anymore.

author: {'steamid': '76561198172052719', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 14, 'playtime_forever': 24, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 24, 'last_played': 1572986993}
review:
As an FPS Veteran - i can only say that the game has great potential.
It has a lot of weapons to chose from => advanced customization on weapons and char.

It has an anti-cheat system.

And the maps are nice and many

The reloading mechanic was unique - pressing R at the right time for faster reload - rarely seen in an FPS

But what i didn`t liked was :

The maps are too small, from the first game i was already camped by the enemy team and the only instance i left the spawn was after i died 4 times.

The community was a lil bit toxic at the first glance - but i will not judge.

The weapons and modifications are kinda overpriced.

From the first game i got placed in a match with experienced players, with weapons, game skills and time better than mine.

I was frequently naded by the enemies.

Rate - 5/10
Not Really

review:
It was worth playing it when I played it back in 2017, 200+ players on at any time.

Now it's dropped to below 50 on average, with less than 150 peak since March 2019.

It also want's a bit of your cash, but it doesn't really detract from the experience. If you get some friends, it's honestly pretty fun, but it's dying.

review:
Although the game holds something different that shows great promise the developers and GM's of the game do not listen enough to the player base about the bugs and problems of the game aside from the fact that there is never a GM around anymore. 
The player base has shrunk so much that there is not enough to support the game so now its in a vicious cycle of not enough money to support the game which means development is so slow. The only reason I play this game now is because of the group I play with but as soon as we find something else that will be a big chunk of people gone and this is what so many others have done.
Nice community its just unfortunate that the development of Line Of Sight is lacking so much.

author: {'steamid': '76561198048893391', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 124, 'playtime_forever': 472, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 323, 'last_played': 1616395345}
review:
Game play is solid,  player base is small, match rewards (have been fixed)

Currency is awarded based on time in the match as well as performance with the time in match being the heavy factor for income.  The game rewards players with enough currency to buy any single gun permanently just by playing a match. Gun costs have come down to a reasonable 17,000 game points.  The game also gives out premium currency for consecutive days played.  

Overall, the game is fun and the developers seem to be listening to critical feedback since changes were made just 2 months after this initial review.


(OPINION - not sure if map is still in game)
The game also has a map called Ground Zero which looks like it takes place in the destroyed area of one of the twin towers which were destroyed in 2001.  I think this is disrespectful to the lives of the 2000 people who died at that location.  And it is for this reason that I will not be playing the game any more.  

Developers, remove Ground Zero from the map selection.  Thank you.

author: {'steamid': '76561198294677975', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 10, 'playtime_forever': 118, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 118, 'last_played': 1560139682}
review: from 100 mins of gameplay, a few things are to note: this game dev really likes csgo, and making guns so similar in damage, that there is no reason to pick any. as a level one, i used an m4 and topfragged an s&d with 12 kills, 4 deaths. my team was gross, and only 2 showed potential.  this game probably was made to gain popularity and then transform into a pay to win. the dev himself isn't much of an fps fanboy, this can be picked up from the fact that every fucking gun apparently has 29 rounds and one in the chamber. which can't even be shot because oh wait. this game doesn't understand chambering. the basis of how all magazine guns work. i don't even want to shoot the chambered bullet i just want to be able to have realism in my game. but for me, once you understand that guns should have 31 rounds, one in the chamber and 30 in the clip,  any game who dare assumes that 30 bullets is all you can have at once, is irrelevant. this game is a mashup of everything i hate about a videogame wrapped in one FTP title. it's skins have value, it's guns have no bullet type, (aside from weather or not to pick ap rounds) i mean cmon it's been a year. you game is hot shit. @dev you are wasting money because of ignorance. play shooters like arma before becoming even confident in choosing what type of game you create

author: {'steamid': '76561198373502045', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 197, 'playtime_forever': 1664, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1610, 'last_played': 1675456109}
review:
I really want to recommend this game but I just canâ€™t at the moment. I enjoy playing it and it brings back so many good memories of MW2 but there are just too many problems with it currently. If the devs fix/change anything I'll update my review.
Pros
Weapon/Character Customization
Not Pay to Win (Yes I'm serious)
Runs good
High TTK
Classic Vibe
Weapon Balance (Pretty good, there are a few weps that need a nerf atm though.)

Cons
Hitreg - Terrible atm, constantly die around corners
Hit boxes - Same with hitreg
Head glitching - Major problem that needs fixing
GP earn rate - Needs to be increased or weapon prices lowered
Mantle/Flash Animation - Are terrible and get you killed so much and need to be removed.
Player falling physics - don't try to slide down a hill
Flashlight - I get its a tactical light but it shouldn't be like looking at the sun
Maps - Pretty meh, a lot of them could use adjusting.
"Super Powers/Abilities" - I hate them, but I play classic anyways
UI - Could be simpler

If you want to read it properly formatted: http://steamcommunity.com/id/Juggernaut_Drive/recommended/436520/

I'll try to expand on my points in case anyone is interested in more of what I mean. Before that however I do want to mention that I do enjoy the game. I enjoy it so much and it reminds me of when I used to play COD all day on xbox when I was a kid. Now to get to the points.

The Pros:
Weapon/Character Customization - Nothing much to say just it's pretty in depth and you can make so many different variants. The only real thing their lacking here are the skins. I assume they will add more skins in time though.
Not Pay to Win - It's not pay to win which is great! People who say it's pay to win don't put any time into the game and look don't at the weapon stats. If you did than you would find out that most of the weapons you buy don't have any better stats that the ones you start with. Now of course there are some weapons that are better than others atm but you get that with every AAA game that has a price tag of ~$60 so I'm sure the developers will address those in the future.
Runs good - Nothing more to say really. It runs good and I have had no problems with it.
High TTK - Very high time to kill which is great. But if you pair that with bad hitreg then you get a load of problems (hitreg is talked about more below).
Classic Vibe - Reminds me of the COD4/MW2 days.
Weapon Balance - As talked about in the not p2w section, weapon balance is pretty good at the time of this review.

The Cons:
Hitreg - It's really bad atm and I mean REALLY bad. Your shots don't hit and you die around corners constantly. I don't know if I just didn't notice it when I first started playing, but I noticed it after one of their updates. So I'm not sure if it was always bad or if that update broke it.
Hit boxes - The female hitbox is smaller than the males (not the bad point) but when you have bad hitreg/head glitching it makes you thing that the hit boxes are also broken. I don't know if itâ€™s that or the hitreg, but something is definitely off.
Head glitching - Major problem that needs fixing. You see the tippy top of their head and they see your whole body. Plus, pair that with the hitboxes and you can't hit their head.
GP earn rate - Needs to be increased or weapon prices lowered. I have around 28 hours into the game (not all playtime) and I currently have around ~170,000 GP. Which seems like a lot of GP but when you add that I played very heavily during the valentine event and the new achievements I got (since it was a new account) it's really not that much. If it wasn't a valentine event and I wasn't a new player I would have significantly less GP for that time played. Yes yes I know you get GP from missions, achievements, leaderboard rankings and at the end of every match.
Missions - Math is based off a 30 day month. So if you do EVERY single mission a month you get around 114,000GP. Daily Missions = 90,000GP, Weekly Missions = 12,000GP, Monthly Missions = 12,000GP. So 1 month of my time isn't worth enough for ONE primary weapon (about 214,000GP)?
Achievements - Yes you get GP for achievements and you get the reward ONCE. This seems good and fair since there are 408 achievements but it's not. More than like half of the achievements are weapon related which means you CAN'T get the reward until you unlock the weapon. The weapons go as follows; K2 I = 30 kills, K2 II = 300 kills, K2 III = 3000 kills. I shouldn't have to say much more about why relying on achievements for GP is so stupid.
Leaderboard - You get 20,000GP if you place in the top 4% in every section every month.
End of match reward - You get like 100GP which is pointless. 1000 games of 100GP = 100,000GP.
Mantle/Flash Animation - Are terrible and get you killed so much and need to be removed. There stupid animations that are not needed. The flash puts a hand up in front of your view and you canâ€™t shoot until the hand goes down. It also lasts LONGER than the actual flash like wtf. The mantle locks you into a mantle animation when you try and jump over something.
Player falling physics - You get stuck and jitter down the hill or object thatâ€™s slanted.
Flash light - I get its a tactical light but it shouldn't be like looking at the sun. It's gameplay breaking, way to bright atm.
Maps - Pretty meh, a lot of them could use adjusting. The S&D maps are by far the best but come with problems as well. A lot of the sites only have 2 entrances and then its closed off.
"Super Powers/Abilities" - Hate them since you need to have the medic one equipped or youâ€™re at a huge disadvantage.
UI - Very confusing when you first load it up and could be simpler.

Battle Royale Mode - I mean, it can only start with 9+ players and that results in a huuuge waiting time.

And this game?
Oh boy, you're in for one hell of a ride!

author: {'steamid': '76561198272710793', 'num_games_owned': 281, 'num_reviews': 19, 'playtime_forever': 280, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 225, 'last_played': 1629575626}
review:
To be honest, the game is complete garbage.
-Almost dead, there are like 4 servers
-The visuals are terrible, tearing and other visual bugs
-The community is 2/3 times non-English speakers
-The hitboxes are complete garbage
-Hackers rampid
-Devs have completely abandoned the game
-Extremely hard to get the money to customize the weapons in the game as well as characters
-All of the guns are the same; one to two shot kills
-Almost non existent recoil for ALL guns
In conclusion:
Its a waste of hard drive space and shouldn't be touched. Just don't even try. Its terrible.

author: {'steamid': '76561198353536384', 'num_games_owned': 146, 'num_reviews': 9, 'playtime_forever': 45, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 45, 'last_played': 1494701725}
review: This game had such good potential, however, the execution was terrible. I saw the game play, and I was impressed. Upon playing it, however, I was very disappointed. The weapons were terrible. They were unbalanced, and very awkward to use. The game mechanics were unbalanced and useless. Using special abilities would sometimes drain the player of his health. The actual game play was not like the trailer at all. The trailer shows very competitive action, while actual game play consists of players spawning all across the map, running to find a fight, dying, then waiting for respawn. It was very boring, as well as grueling, and I had a better time watching paint dry than attempting to play this game. If you want to get a free FPS, I would suggest Counter Strike: Global Offensive, Warface, Black Squad, or Dirty Bomb. Do not waste time on this game.

author: {'steamid': '76561198057040916', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 56424, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 54686, 'last_played': 1550799451}
review:
Don't waste your time on playing this game. For a long time devs only add new items to buy for real money instead of fixing annoying bugs or adding new content etc.
Generally the game is managed badly, e.g.: Recently they organized an event that players could win real money by playing. It seemed nice at first. But it was SCAM in some way. They announced winners only in Steam Announcements (not in game, nor Facebook etc.), in an unexpected random day, quite a long time after event, and they set the deadline to claim the awards only to next day, so there was to little time to even notice this announcement.

author: {'steamid': '76561198193223709', 'num_games_owned': 332, 'num_reviews': 72, 'playtime_forever': 896, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 573, 'last_played': 1657898925}
review:
Pay To Win under disguise!

At the start of the game, you can't buy any guns except for a few, which are lackluster!
You are given a few guns for 30 days which will then expire, and then you'll be stuck with the Training M4 which cannot be tuned. That means you can't attach a scope or anything like that, which will then get you killed as the long range targets will be very hard to shoot. There's a lot of long range shooting, camping, and sniping in this game. Also as a new player you will be put against the high level players who have unlocked the better guns. Earning enough gold to buy a gun after it becomes unlockable for gold when you level up will take forever as well! That's right, if you want to get good gear to be able compete better at the start when you're going up against the pros who will beat you anyway; expect to pay real cash! This game is absolutely trash and the developers are unashamed to lie about it! Oh and by the way, you can't rent weapons to try them out and there's no selling back attachments or guns if you accidentally buy the wrong item. Matchmaking well is trash, like I mentioned before you'll get put against pro but also the game is almost dead.

The only good thing is the customization. If you want a scope on a Glock 18, you can put one on it although that would be perfectly useless as it can't shoot that far.

The graphics are just ok, there's plenty of vegetation but it's all low res compared to newer titles. At least the game is very passable graphically due to it's small download size.

Overall -666/5 stars!



Do yourself a favor and play other FREE games instead, emphasis on FREE!

Completely free games, no microtransactions, no DLC, no purchases of any sort!

author: {'steamid': '76561198057894301', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 54, 'playtime_forever': 29, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 29, 'last_played': 1544354427}
review: Play another and better online FPS. I just felt like trying this cause back then when I felt like trying Crossfire, Counter Strike, A.V.A I had a good time. The controls are just so clunky and feels so stiff, you can't switch to knife instantly after firing a sniper shot. And the maps are way too small. Go ahead and play a FFA mode, chances are you will be randomyl spawned behind an enemy you're not even aware of and get killed after just taking a few steps. The team deathmatches are ok but the maps are just way too small. There is no room for strategy, just spray your bullets, throw grenades and hopefully somebody will get killed. This game still needs some work, some fine tuning.

author: {'steamid': '76561198253821354', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 1264, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1249, 'last_played': 1541058064}
review:
I've seen a lot of negative reviews on the game and I definitely want to set some things straigh.

First off, this game is NOT pay to win, every gun is achievable through playing the game and grinding quests for money. And even if you bought all this in game currency with real life money you would still have to play the game a crap ton to level up to unlock any of the guns. 

The game isn't exactly unbalanced either, between my group of friends I'm know for being the guy who complains about the smallest problems in video games but weapon balance is just fine in this game, some guns deal less than others, but that's often justified by higher firerate or less recoil. And you die very quickly in this game if you get shot anyway so any gun can get you a win if you put your sweaty tryhard pants on. (Which is actually a fun thing to do in this game)

Next thing is hackers, I still actively play this game and I promise to update this part of the review AS SOON as I see a hacker in this game, but so far I haven't met a single hacker, just good players. 

Don't decide not to install this game just because people say it's "dead", you can join the game at any time around the clock and there will always be at least one server with players in it, during weekdays it's very often 3-6 servers and on weekends double that. And you can only play on one server at a time anyway so it's really not that big of a deal! 

This game could easily have a 70+ positive review rate if all the old and dumb reviews about "script kiddies" and "the game is dead" were gone. 

And did I mention that this game runs on literally anything? Back when all I had was a Dell Optiplex office computer with an integrated video processing unit and not an actual graphics card I could still run this game. 

I hope at least someone sees this review as it clears out most of the negative reviews on this game as this game really deserves more.
